    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 2.5 Pro</div>
    <h1>CrowdStrike (CRWD)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of CrowdStrike Holdings — using FY2026 actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026 · Data: FY2026 10-K</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$4.81B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY2026 Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$1.31B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$-0.65</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">27.2%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FCF Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>CrowdStrike generated <strong>$1.31 billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2026. This represents a 27.2% FCF margin, highlighting the underlying cash generation capacity of its software-as-a-service (SaaS) model.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>20% per year</strong> for the next 5 years. While revenue growth has historically been in the 30-50% range, it decelerated to ~21% in FY2026. A 20% growth rate captures CrowdStrike's leading position in endpoint security while adjusting for the law of large numbers and macroeconomic factors.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3.5% forever</strong> — slightly above GDP growth, accounting for CrowdStrike's continued pricing power and structural importance in enterprise IT security. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>10%</strong> — our required rate of return. This aligns with the long-term historical returns of the equity market and incorporates a reasonable equity risk premium over the 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash ($4.41B) = Equity Value. Divide by diluted shares outstanding (252M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">20%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        CrowdStrike's revenue growth decelerated to 21.7% in FY2026. However, its FCF margins remain incredibly strong at 27.2%. We forecast 20% annual FCF growth as the company continues to penetrate the cybersecurity market, expand modules (like identity and cloud security), and leverage its operating model, balancing maturing growth with cash flow expansion.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">10%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. Equity risk premium: ~5.5%. Given CrowdStrike's high beta typical of high-growth software, CAPM could suggest a higher rate. However, its strong net cash position and sticky, mission-critical product mitigate some risk. We use 10% as a standard institutional hurdle rate for large-cap tech.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.5%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Cybersecurity is not a discretionary expense; it's a structural requirement. We assign a 3.5% perpetuity growth rate (0.5% premium to long-term nominal GDP) to reflect CrowdStrike's lasting competitive moat and secular tailwinds in threat intelligence and endpoint protection.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (FY2026)</td>
          <td>${fcfBase.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year} ({2026 + p.year})</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × 1.035)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ (10% − 3.5%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
