      <div class="faq-answer">The market often prices high-growth tech stocks based on optimistic future scenarios or momentum rather than conservative, risk-adjusted cash flows. Investors buying at $440+ are implicitly assuming FCF growth closer to 30-40% for the next 5-10 years, or a much lower discount rate. Our model requires a 10% return and 20% growth, resulting in a lower intrinsic value.</div>
