    <details>
      <summary>Why use FCF when earnings (EPS) are negative?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Earnings are an accounting metric distorted by non-cash charges like depreciation, amortization, and massive Stock-Based Compensation (SBC). FCF measures the actual cash entering the bank account. For SaaS companies like CrowdStrike, FCF is a much more reliable indicator of business health.</div>
    </details>
